<section>
<p style="Heading 1">Page Numbers Dialog</p>
<p style="Normal"><c style="Normal">This dialog inserts page numbers on every page of your document.</c></p>
<p style="Heading 2"><c style="Heading 2">Position</c></p>
<p style="Normal"><c style="Normal">The drop-down menu here allows you to choose whether the page numbers appear in the header of the document, or the footer.</c></p>
<p style="Heading 2"><c style="Heading 2">Alignment</c></p>
<p style="Normal"><c style="Normal">The drop down menu for Alignment determines whether the page numbers are placed at the left,  right, or center of the header or footer.</c></p>
<p style="Heading 2"><c style="Heading 2">Preview</c></p>
<p style="Normal"><c style="Normal">This display shows the selected position of the page number relative to the main text of the page.</c></p>
<p style="Heading 2"><c style="Heading 2">OK</c></p>
<p style="Normal"><c style="Normal">This button inserts the page numbers and closes the dialog.</c></p>
<p style="Heading 2"><c style="Heading 2">Cancel</c></p>
<p style="Normal"><c style="Normal">This button closes the dialog without inserting the page numbers.</c></p>
</section>
